definitions.definition: One of the six federal states of Australia , consisting of one large, eponymous and several much smaller islands, off the eastern part of Australia's south coast; a former British colony , from 1856 to 1901. Capital: Hobart .
The large island of Australia comprising the majority of the state of Tasmania's land area and on which most of its inhabitants live.
